
My Step By Step WordPress Theme Development Checklist:


1. Configure Local Development Environment:
    a.	Set Up LOCAL by FlyWheel.
    b.	Install & Set Up WordPress.
    c.	Configure VS Code + Extensions.

 
2. Basic WordPress Theme Structure:
    a.	Create The Theme with _UnderScore.com
    b.	Setup Style.CSS
    c.  Add Theme Support Functions that muste be included in Function while 
        Theme Development. So add these following function at Strart before working on Development of new Theme.
        {
        add_theme_support('title_tag');
        add_theme_support('post_thumbnails');
        add_theme_support('post_formats', ['aside','gallery','link','status','video','audio','image','quote','chat']);
        add_theme_support('html5');
        add_theme_support('automatic_feed_links');
        add_theme_support('custom-logo');
        add_theme_support('custom-header');
        add_theme_support('custom-background');
        add_theme_support('starter-content');
        }
        /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
    d.	Enqueue or Link required Scripts.(Functions. CSS, JavaScript, Font-Awesome,). add_action HOOK.
    e. set up Header and Footer .php files with Functions-> wp_head() & wp_footer() .
    f. Complete Fully Responsive Structure before Working on Content/ Header/SideBars etc.
    	
    g. Create/Add Navigation Menus(Register_Nav_Menus) in Functions.php(Header/Footer Menu). //Register_nav_Menu();
    Register The Menu fist in Functions.php and then define it in Header.php to display on website.
    h. Create/ Register SideBar for Widget Areas in Functions.php
    i.	

3.Advanced Functions For Building Theme Main Content Page: Working With Loop
    a. The WordPress Loop. Get_Post Function in Index.php
    b. Check Template Hierarchy.
    c. Template_Part Folder.
    d. Confirm Custom Pages. (Page Templates ).
    e. Comments.PHP Impot from TwentySeventeen Theme. 
    f.	WP Loop(Default Loop) VS WP Query Loop(Custom Loop).

4. Create Inner Pages:
    a.	Permalinks of Theme Links.
    b.	Single Post Template.
    c.	Add Comments Section in Single Posts.
    d.	Add Search Functionality in Theme.
    e.	Add Pagination in Blog Page, Search Page and Single Post Page.
    f.	Configure One Archive Page for Categories, Tags and Authors etc.
    g.	Create & Design 404 Page for Broken Link Pages.
    h.	The Widget Function for 404 Page.
    i.	The Template_Part() Function.
    j.	Conditional Tags for Header Menu Showing, Landing Page etc.
    k.	WP_Body_Open() Function for Integrating Tools Like Google Analytics, Adsense, GTM, and Google Search Console etc.


5. WordPress HOOKS (Most Important).


6. 




Page Templates:

Index.php

Singular.php

Single.php

Home.php


